115
00:15:09,991 --> 00:15:11,720
I don't wanna see you anymore.

116
00:15:11,893 --> 00:15:14,225
- Telly, wait.
- The book...

117
00:15:14,396 --> 00:15:16,956
The book, I can lose, but...

118
00:15:19,234 --> 00:15:21,463
You erased our son.

119
00:15:21,635 --> 00:15:24,627
You erased my boy.
You made it all blank.

120
00:15:24,805 --> 00:15:27,797
- You took him away.
- Stop. They were always blank.

121
00:15:27,975 --> 00:15:32,206
- What? What are you saying?
- You're healing. You're coming back.

122
00:15:32,378 --> 00:15:35,040
- Dr. Munce is coming.
- Let me go! Let me go!

123
00:15:35,215 --> 00:15:38,480
This is good.
God, Telly, this is real.

124
00:15:38,651 --> 00:15:41,245
The tapes were always blank.

125
00:15:42,388 --> 00:15:44,582
Do you know what he's telling me?

126
00:15:45,324 --> 00:15:46,689
Yes.

127
00:15:47,826 --> 00:15:49,589
Is he psychotic?

128
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:52,888
No.

129
00:15:55,566 --> 00:15:57,397
My child.

130
00:15:58,636 --> 00:16:00,900
My Sam.

131
00:16:01,973 --> 00:16:03,531
Telly.

132
00:16:04,342 --> 00:16:07,333
There was never a Sam Paretta.

133
00:16:08,144 --> 00:16:09,509
You never had a son.

134
00:16:10,947 --> 00:16:12,676
- This is insane.
- I'm so sorry.

135
00:16:12,849 --> 00:16:14,817
I wanted to help you slowly.

136
00:16:14,985 --> 00:16:17,817
- Gently. But I never thought you...
- He erased the tapes.

137
00:16:17,987 --> 00:16:20,387
