How can you believe him?

138
00:16:20,556 --> 00:16:22,456
Sam, he grew up. He was 9.

139
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:24,923
Nine. I had nine years of memories.

140
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:27,128
Invented memories, Telly.
It happens.

141
00:16:27,296 --> 00:16:29,820
People do this.
It's called paramnesia.

142
00:16:29,998 --> 00:16:32,330
- You imagined a life...
- Everyone remembers Sam.

143
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,933
- Everyone.
- Telly.

144
00:16:34,102 --> 00:16:35,433
You had a miscarriage.

145
00:16:35,603 --> 00:16:38,470
Your life was in danger.
The baby was premature.

146
00:16:38,773 --> 00:16:42,674
- It was stillborn. You almost died.
- Stop it.

147
00:16:42,843 --> 00:16:45,539
Post-traumatic shock.
It affects everyone differently.

148
00:16:45,712 --> 00:16:48,772
Some people actually invent
entire alternate lives...

149
00:16:48,949 --> 00:16:51,382
...with imagined friends
and lovers and children.

150
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:54,883
Stop. Why are you doing this?
Why are you trying to take him away?

151
00:16:55,054 --> 00:16:57,784
