177
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:56,285
How could it not be
in any of these?

178
00:19:56,453 --> 00:19:58,478
You sure of the date?

179
00:20:00,623 --> 00:20:02,317
What are you trying to find?

180
00:20:02,491 --> 00:20:06,018
"Six Brooklyn Children Feared Dead
in Missing Plane".

181
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:10,127
How could it not...?

182
00:20:11,066 --> 00:20:12,294
I have to go.

183
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:14,898
I have to go.

184
00:20:34,654 --> 00:20:36,644
- Eliot.
- Christ.

185
00:20:36,822 --> 00:20:38,983
Telly. What are you doing
in the dark?

186
00:20:39,158 --> 00:20:40,591
What's wrong?

187
00:20:40,759 --> 00:20:42,226
I had a fight with Jim.

188
00:20:42,495 --> 00:20:44,326
Oh, I'm sorry. Come inside.

189
00:20:44,497 --> 00:20:46,488
We fought about Sam.

190
00:20:47,398 --> 00:20:48,626
I'm sorry, about what?

191
00:20:50,468 --> 00:20:52,561
Sam.

192
00:20:52,904 --> 00:20:54,769
Sam. Who's Sam, sweetie?

193
00:20:55,740 --> 00:20:58,674
Eliot, he's my son.

194
00:20:59,176 --> 00:21:00,700
Your son?

195
00:21:01,411 --> 00:21:03,311
El, please.

196
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:06,278
You knew my son.
You babysat him a thousand times.

197
00:21:06,450 --> 00:21:09,418
- I don't know what you're trying to say.
- You knew my son.

198
00:21:09,585 --> 00:21:12,019
You talked to him,
you took him to a Mets game...

199
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,622
